result.execSummary:
All charges against Anthony D Taylor in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Anthony D Taylor is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Attorney Angel L Johnson in court, defendant Anthony D Taylor not in court, in custody.  Mario Fiumefreddo appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Attorney appeared by video means.  Defendant violated conditions of Extended Supervision (related to Sheboygan County Case 17CF627) and is commanded to return to the Wisconsin Dodge Correctional Institution.  On State's motion, Court ordered case dismissed.

Defendant Anthony D Taylor in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Defendant Anthony D Taylor in custody.  Karine O'Byrne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Anthony D Taylor appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Kies, Branch 45.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of Texas.  Defendant waived extradition.  Signed Waiver of Extradition received and filed.
